# Java Inheritance Example

Here's a practical example demonstrating inheritance in Java:

```java
// Parent class (Superclass)
class Animal {
    private String name;
    private int age;

    // Constructor
    public Animal(String name, int age) {
        this.name = name;
        this.age = age;
    }

    // Methods
    public void sleep() {
        System.out.println(name + " is sleeping...");
    }

    public void eat(String food) {
        System.out.println(name + " is eating " + food);
    }

    // Getter methods
    public String getName() {
        return name;
    }

    public int getAge() {
        return age;
    }
}

// Child class (Subclass) inheriting from Animal
class Dog extends Animal {
    private String breed;

    // Constructor
    public Dog(String name, int age, String breed) {
        super(name, age);  // Call parent constructor
        this.breed = breed;
    }

    // Override parent method
    @Override
    public void sleep() {
        System.out.println(getName() + " is sleeping in the doghouse...");
    }

    // New method specific to Dog
    public void bark() {
        System.out.println(getName() + " says: Woof! Woof!");
    }

    public String getBreed() {
        return breed;
    }
}

// Another child class
class Cat extends Animal {

    public Cat(String name, int age) {
        super(name, age);
    }

    @Override
    public void sleep() {
        System.out.println(getName() + " is napping on the couch...");
    }

    public void meow() {
        System.out.println(getName() + " says: Meow!");
    }
}

// Main class to demonstrate usage
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Create Dog object
        Dog dog = new Dog("Buddy", 5, "Golden Retriever");
        dog.eat("bones");        // Inherited method
        dog.bark();              // Dog-specific method
        dog.sleep();             // Overridden method

        System.out.println();

        // Create Cat object
        Cat cat = new Cat("Whiskers", 3);
        cat.eat("fish");         // Inherited method
        cat.meow();              // Cat-specific method
        cat.sleep();             // Overridden method
    }
}
```

## Output:
```
Buddy is eating bones
Buddy says: Woof! Woof!
Buddy is sleeping in the doghouse...

Whiskers is eating fish
Whiskers says: Meow!
Whiskers is napping on the couch...
```

## Key Concepts Demonstrated:

| Concept | Explanation |
|---------|-------------|
| **extends** | Dog and Cat inherit from Animal |
| **super()** | Calls parent class constructor |
| **@Override** | Indicates method is overridden from parent |
| **Inheritance** | Dog and Cat reuse `eat()` and `sleep()` methods |
| **Polymorphism** | `sleep()` behaves differently for each subclass |

This example shows how inheritance allows code reuse and creates a logical hierarchy!
